text: thumb Sarah Myriam Mazouz (born April 29, 1987) is a Gabonese judoka. She competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the women's 78 kg event, in which she was eliminated in the second round by Natalie Powell. She also won the gold medal in the women's 78 kg event at the 2019 African Games. ==References== Category:1987 births Category:Living people Category:Gabonese female judoka Category:Olympic judoka of Gabon Category:Judoka at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Competitors at the 2019 African Games Category:African Games gold medalists for Gabon Category:African Games medalists in judo Category:African Games competitors for Gabon
